node.text:
The night of our engagement, I planned a surprise engagement party for Alex. [Arguably harder to keep a secret than the ring itself!] She thought we were going to dinner, just the two of us, and that our engagement was still a secret that only her and I (and our photographer who we had a shoot with that day) knew about.
All of our closest friends and family made the trip to come and celebrate with us, and I can’t begin to tell you how special that was. Each hug was felt, every laugh was deep, and I don’t know if I’ve ever felt so loved.
We had the best day ever.
.
Thanks for capturing this night @tampajordan.

node.text:
Love this photo dump “trend.”
Ive always tried to treat Instagram sorta like a scrapbook that I’ll have for years and years. I look back at photos often and try to relive little moments in my head from that memory, and it makes me happy. Life really is a collection of little moments, and sometimes we’re lucky enough to catch them in a photo.❤️
Here’s a little dumpy from St. Augustine where we took my mom to celebrate the big 6-0 a couple weeks ago.

node.text:
*wants more tattoos*
.
Proud of this @alphaforward launch we got goin on tomorrow. It’s always like Christmas morning to see something you drew on paper, or put together in your head, come to fruition.
It’s worth all the roadblocks you have to barrel through during  the process. I wish y’all could see what goes into it. Each item. If you knew, you’d prob never get into clothing 😂.
Thank you in advance to anyone who snags somethin or just wishes me well! #livingthedream

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Evan Childs on May 18, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, biceps, standing and indoor.

node.text:
Brain dump: 🧠 
.
.
How blessed are we, that we to GET TO move these bodies of ours?
Yes, life happens, and fitness sometimes takes a backseat to it, but I encourage you to give SOMETHING. Do SOMETHING. Move. Give back to your blessing of health. It will help so many aspects of your life. I am a testament to that. A lot of you know I took some time off from the gym recently. Started back up hard about 9 weeks ago.
I learned a lot during that time.
.
I didn’t feel like myself.
I wasn’t as confident.
I wasn’t as productive.
I wasn’t as balanced.
.
My mental health slipped due to all of the above. We all deal with shit. All of us. And a way to reduce it is to MOVE. It’s clear our bodies were meant to. Doesn’t have to be a triathlon every weekend or a 5am class every morning. Just move. However you like to. 
.
I also want to say.. To chase after the “perfect body” is an unconquerable quest that your human psyche wouldn’t allow anyway. [Stop comparing yourself to insta.]
But.. to chase after YOUR best body is a quest that can be accomplished with time. We all have different shapes, heights, sizes, genetics. That individuality is also a blessing! Take pride in being YOU.. and MOVE.

I hope Elon’s right about life eventually being multi-planetary so I can say you’re the best mom on the face of all planets.

Happy momma’s day. Can’t wait to see you soon! 💐
